<h2 class="display-6">
    Basic Syntax 
</h2>

<p>
    Css has a nice syntax that uses the tag name followed by curly brackets <code>{}</code>. 
    The actual styling elements are separated by semicolons and the key-value pairs are 
    separated by colons. 
    <pre><code class="lang-css">p {
    color: red;
}</code></pre>
</p>


<p style="color: red">
    Now the text color of &lt;p&gt; is red. 
</p>

<h3>
    Classes
</h3>
<p>
    Use dot <code>.</code> notation before the class name to 
    access a class. 
</p>  
<pre><code class="lang-css">.column {
    max-width: 20%;
} 
</code></pre>

<h3>IDs</h3>
<p>
    Use a hashtag <code>#</code> before the element name to access an element by ID. 
</p>  
<pre><code class="lang-css">
#tableOfContents {
    color: red;
} 
</code></pre>
